org.bk.ass.manage

Class GMSReservation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bk.ass.manage.GMSReservation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Reservation<GMS>

    public class GMSReservation
extends java.lang.Object
implements Reservation<GMS>
    Reservation implementation for GMS. Can be used for tracking the remaining available resources. (Ie. start each frame by setGms(GMS) using the current amount of resources, then use GMS-Locks to track reservations.)

      • reserve

        public boolean reserve(java.lang.Object source,
                       GMS gmsToReserve)
        Description copied from interface: Reservation
        Returns true, if the given item is available immediately. Returns false, if the item was reserved but is not yet available. (Ie. resources might be "blocked" for later use, but not yet spendable.)
        Specified by:

      • itemAvailableInFuture

        public boolean itemAvailableInFuture(java.lang.Object source,
                                     GMS futureItem,
                                     int futureFrames)
        Description copied from interface: Reservation
        Returns true if the given item will be available in futureFrames frames. The given item will already be reserved when this is called! If used for GMS, you should re-add the given GMS before checking for sufficient resources.
